# Operational Model

## Workweek

A workweek:

- is agency-configured
- defaults to Monday
- may start on any weekday
- exists primarily for:
  - overtime
  - weekly timesheets
  - reporting

Workweeks are distinct from pay periods.

---

## Pay Period

A pay period:

- is a persisted operational payroll record
- is automatically generated
- supports payroll summaries
- supports payroll exports
- supports payroll reporting
- supports Team360 visibility

MVP frequencies:

- weekly
- biweekly
- semimonthly
- monthly

Semimonthly periods use fixed halves:

| Period | Dates |
| --- | --- |
| First | 1st–15th |
| Second | 16th–end of month |

---

# Lifecycle

## States

| Status | Meaning |
| --- | --- |
| `open` | Editable operational payroll period |
| `closed` | Finalized payroll-processing-complete period |

---

## Open periods

Open periods:

- allow time corrections
- allow approvals
- allow leave integration
- allow payroll exports
- allow multiple draft exports

---

## Closed periods

Closed periods:

- represent finalized payroll-processing posture
- become immutable by default
- should block standard editing
- may support future administrative reopening

---

# Overtime Rules

## MVP overtime

MVP supports weekly overtime only.

### Rules

- Overtime is based on worked hours only.
- Leave/PTO does not contribute toward overtime thresholds.
- Overtime is derived from approved worked time.
- Overtime visibility is continuous during the period.

### Agency configuration

| Setting | Default |
| --- | --- |
| `weekly_overtime_threshold_hours` | `40` |

Future advanced overtime rules are deferred.

---

# Payroll Summary Structure

| Field | Meaning |
| --- | --- |
| `regular_hours` | Approved worked non-overtime hours |
| `overtime_hours` | Approved overtime worked hours |
| `leave_hours` | Approved payable leave hours |
| `total_paid_hours` | Regular + overtime + payable leave |

---

# Payroll Export Posture

## Draft exports

Open periods may generate multiple draft exports.

## Final export

The export associated with pay-period closure becomes the authoritative finalized export artifact.

Exports should remain historically visible.

---

# Closure Rules

## Closure validation

Periods should not close when:

- missing timesheets exist
- pending approvals exist

## Override

Administrative override is allowed.

## Authority

Closure authority is capability/permission-based.

---

# Contractor Separation

Employee payroll periods remain distinct from contractor settlement cycles.

TC-23a intentionally avoids unifying:

- payroll periods
- contractor settlement periods
- contractor settlement exports

---

# Reporting Expectations

TC-23a supports future reporting for:

- current pay-period status
- missing timesheets
- pending approvals
- overtime visibility
- payroll export history
- employee hour summaries
- employee timesheets

---

# Future-Compatible Areas

TC-23a must leave room for:

- payroll groups
- multiple payroll schedules
- advanced overtime rules
- retro payroll adjustments
- multi-state employees
- scheduling integration
- contractor time workflows
- accrual engines
- payroll APIs

without requiring foundational redesign.